gingly-written book demonstrates that a Jewish movie is neither just a movie nor for Jews only. With incisive analysis, Movie-Made Jews challenges the assumption that American Jewish cinema is a cinema of impoverishment and assimilation. While it’s a truism that Jews make movies, this book brings into focus the diverse ways movies make Jews.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aJews in motion pictures. 0aJews in the motion picture industry. 0aJewszUnited StatesxIdentity. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican Jewish, cinema, movies, fiction, antisemitism, Holocaust, assimilation, immigrant, queer, race, religion, film, film studies, media studies, communications, postwar media, LGBTQ, stereotypical roles, jazz, jazz singers, pawnbrokers, whiteness, racism, antisemites, Zion, School Ties, Liberty Heights, feminism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882192740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978821927423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978821927/original  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_P